              'summary': '<p>In accordance with <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/stable/internals/security/">our '
                         'security release policy</a>, the Django team\n'
                         'is issuing releases for\n'
                         '<a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/stable/releases/6.0.3/">Django '
                         '6.0.3</a>,\n'
                         '<a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/stable/releases/5.2.12/">Django '
                         '5.2.12</a>, and\n'
                         '<a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/stable/releases/4.2.29/">Django '
                         '4.2.29</a>.\n'
                         'These releases address the security issues detailed '
                         'below. We encourage all\n'
                         'users of Django to upgrade as soon as possible.</p>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2026-25673-potential-denial-of-service-vulnerability-in-urlfield-via-unicode-normalization-on-windows">\n'
                         '<h3>CVE-2026-25673: Potential denial-of-service '
                         'vulnerability in <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">URLField</tt> via Unicode normalization on '
                         'Windows</h3>\n'
                         '<p>The <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">django.forms.URLField</tt> form field\'s '
                         '<tt class="docutils literal">to_python()</tt> method '
                         'used\n'
                         '<tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">urllib.parse.urlsplit()</tt> to determine '
                         'whether to prepend a URL scheme to\n'
                         'the submitted value. On Windows, <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">urlsplit()</tt> performs\n'
                         'NFKC normalization (<tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">unicodedata.normalize</tt>), which can be\n'
                         'disproportionately slow for large inputs containing '
                         'certain characters.</p>\n'
                         '<p><tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">URLField.to_python()</tt> now uses a '
                         'simplified scheme detection, avoiding\n'
                         'Unicode normalization entirely and deferring URL '
                         'validation to the appropriate\n'
                         'layers. As a result, while leading and trailing '
                         'whitespace is still stripped by\n'
                         'default, characters such as newlines, tabs, and '
                         'other control characters within\n'
                         'the value are no longer handled by <tt '
                         'class="docutils literal">URLField.to_python()</tt>. '
                         'When using the\n'
                         'default <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">URLValidator</tt>, these values will '
                         'continue to raise <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">ValidationError</tt>\n'
                         'during validation, but if you rely on custom '
                         'validators, ensure they do not\n'
                         'depend on the previous behavior of <tt '
                         'class="docutils '
                         'literal">URLField.to_python()</tt>.</p>\n'
                         '<p>This issue has severity &quot;moderate&quot; '
                         'according to the Django Security Policy.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Thanks to Seokchan Yoon for the report.</p>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2026-25674-potential-incorrect-permissions-on-newly-created-file-system-objects">\n'
                         '<h3>CVE-2026-25674: Potential incorrect permissions '
                         'on newly created file system objects</h3>\n'
                         "<p>Django's file-system storage and file-based cache "
                         'backends used the process\n'
                         '<tt class="docutils literal">umask</tt> to control '
                         'permissions when creating directories. In '
                         'multi-threaded\n'
                         "environments, one thread's temporary umask change "
                         "can affect other threads'\n"
                         'file and directory creation, resulting in file '
                         'system objects being created\n'
                         'with unintended permissions.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Django now applies the requested permissions via '
                         '<tt class="docutils literal">os.chmod()</tt> after\n'
                         '<tt class="docutils literal">os.mkdir()</tt>, '
                         'removing the dependency on the process-wide '
                         'umask.</p>\n'
                         '<p>This issue has severity &quot;low&quot; according '
                         'to the Django Security Policy.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Thanks to Tarek Nakkouch for the report.</p>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
