                                          'in front the camera, smiling, with '
                                          'his computer in his hand. He wears '
                                          'a yellow and green plaid shirt, a '
                                          'green T-shirt with DjangoCon '
                                          'visible, and green pants. His '
                                          'computer is covered with '
                                          'Django-related stickers." '
                                          'src="https://media.djangoproject.com/blog/images/2026/02/baptiste-mispelon-standing-with-his-computer.jpg" '
                                          '/>\n'
                                          '<em>Photo by Bartek Pawlik - <a '
                                          'href="https://bartpawlik.format.com/">bartpawlik.format.com</a></em></p>\n'
                                          '<p>Baptiste is a long-time Django '
                                          'and Python contributor who '
                                          'co-created the Django Under the '
                                          'Hood conference series and serves '
                                          'on the Ops team maintaining its '
                                          'infrastructure. He has been a DSF '
                                          'member since November 2014.\n'
                                          'You can learn more about Baptiste '
                                          'by visiting <a '
                                          'href="https://blog.bmispelon.rocks/">Baptiste\'s '
                                          'website</a> and <a '
                                          'href="https://github.com/bmispelon">his '
                                          'GitHub Profile</a>.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Let’s spend some time getting to '
                                          'know Baptiste better!</p>\n'
                                          '<h4 '
                                          'id="s-can-you-tell-us-a-little-about-yourself-hobbies-education-etc">Can '
                                          'you tell us a little about '
                                          'yourself? (hobbies, education, '
                                          'etc)</h4>\n'
                                          "<p>I'm a French immigrant living in "
                                          'Norway. In the day time I work as '
                                          'software engineer at <a '
                                          'href="https://torchbox.com/">Torchbox</a> '
                                          'building Django and Wagtail sites.\n'
                                          'Education-wise I\'m a "self-taught" '
                                          '(whatever that means) developer and '
                                          'started working when I was very '
                                          'young.\n'
                                          "In terms of hobbies, I'm a big "
                                          "language nerd and I'm always up for "
                                          'a good etymology fact. I also enjoy '
                                          "the outdoor whether it's on a "
                                          'mountain bike or on foot (still not '
                                          'convinced by this skiing thing they '
                                          "do in Norway, but I'm trying).</p>\n"
                                          '<h4 '
                                          'id="s-how-did-you-start-using-django">How '
                                          'did you start using Django?</h4>\n'
                                          '<p>I was working in a startup where '
                                          'I had built an unmaintainable pile '
                                          'of custom framework-less PHP code. '
                                          "I'd heard of this cool Python "
                                          'framework and thought it would help '
                                          'me bring some structure to our '
                                          'codebase. So I started rewriting '
                                          'our services bit-by-bit and '
                                          'eventually switched everything to '
                                          'Django after about a year.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>In 2012, I bought a ticket to '
                                          'DjangoCon Europe in Zurich and went '
                                          'there not knowing anyone. It was '
                                          'one of the best decisions of my '
                                          'life: the Django community welcomed '
                                          'me and has given me so much over '
                                          'the years.</p>\n'
                                          '<h4 '
                                          'id="s-what-other-framework-do-you-know-and-if-there-is-anything-you-would-like-to-have-in-django-if-you-had-magical-powers">What '
                                          'other framework do you know and if '
                                          'there is anything you would like to '
                                          'have in Django if you had magical '
                                          'powers?</h4>\n'
                                          "<p>I've been making website for "
                                          "more than two decades now, so I've "
                                          'used my fair share of various '
                                          'technologies and frameworks, but '
                                          'Django is still my "daily driver" '
                                          'and the one I like the best. I like '
                                          'writing plain CSS, and when I need '
                                          'some extra bit of JS I like to use '
                                          'Alpine JS and/or HTMX: I find they '
                                          'work really well together with '
                                          'Django.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>If I had magical powers and '
                                          'could change anything, I would '
                                          'remove the word "patch" from '
                                          'existence (and especially from the '
                                          'Django documentation).</p>\n'
