              'published_parsed': time.struct_time(tm_year=2026, tm_mon=2, tm_mday=19, tm_hour=15, tm_min=51, tm_sec=0, tm_wday=3, tm_yday=50, tm_isdst=0),
              'summary': '<p>Last month <a '
                         'href="https://forum.djangoproject.com/t/updating-the-code-of-conduct/43924">we '
                         'announced our plan</a> to adopt <a '
                         'href="https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/3/0/code_of_conduct/">Contributor '
                         "Covenant 3</a> as Django's new Code of Conduct "
                         "through a multi-step process. Today we're excited to "
                         "share that we've completed the first step of that "
                         'journey!</p>\n'
                         '<h4 id="s-what-weve-done">What We\'ve Done</h4>\n'
                         "<p>We've merged <a "
                         'href="https://github.com/django/code-of-conduct/blob/main/updates.md">new '
                         'documentation</a> that outlines how any member of '
                         'the Django community can propose changes to our Code '
                         'of Conduct and related policies. This creates a '
                         'transparent, community-driven process for keeping '
                         'our policies current and relevant.</p>\n'
                         '<p>The new process includes:</p>\n'
                         '<ul>\n'
                         '<li><strong>Proposing Changes</strong>: Anyone can '
                         '<a '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/code-of-conduct/issues/new?template=coc-change-proposal.md">open '
                         'an issue</a> with a clear description of their '
                         'proposed change and the rationale behind it.</li>\n'
                         '<li><strong>Community Review</strong>: The Code of '
                         'Conduct Working Group will discuss proposals in our '
                         'monthly meetings and may solicit broader community '
                         'feedback through the forum, Discord, or DSF '
                         'Slack.</li>\n'
                         '<li><strong>Approval and Announcement</strong>: Once '
                         'consensus is reached, changes are merged and '
                         'announced to the community. Changes to the Code of '
                         'Conduct itself will be sent to the DSF Board for '
                         'final approval.</li>\n'
                         '</ul>\n'
                         '<h4 id="s-how-you-can-get-involved">How You Can Get '
                         'Involved</h4>\n'
                         '<p>We welcome and encourage participation from '
                         "everyone in the Django community! Here's how you can "
                         'engage with this process:</p>\n'
                         '<ul>\n'
                         '<li><strong>Share Your Ideas</strong>: If you have '
                         'suggestions for improving our Code of Conduct or '
                         'related documentation, <a '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/code-of-conduct/issues/new?template=coc-change-proposal.md">open '
                         'an issue</a> on our GitHub repo.</li>\n'
                         '<li><strong>Join the Discussion</strong>: '
                         'Participate in community discussions about proposed '
                         'changes on the forum, Discord, or DSF Slack. Keep it '
                         'positive, constructive, and respectful.</li>\n'
                         '<li><strong>Stay Informed</strong>: Watch the <a '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/code-of-conduct">Code '
                         'of Conduct repository</a> to follow along with '
                         'proposed changes and discussions.</li>\n'
                         '<li><strong>Provide Feedback</strong>: Not '
                         'comfortable with GitHub? You can also reach out via '
                         '<a '
                         'href="mailto:conduct@djangoproject.com">conduct@djangoproject.com</a>, '
                         'or look for anyone with the <code>Code of Conduct '
                         'WG</code> role on Discord.</li>\n'
                         '</ul>\n'
                         '<h4 id="s-whats-next">What\'s Next</h4>\n'
                         "<p>We're moving forward with the remaining steps of "
                         'our plan:</p>\n'
                         '<ul>\n'
                         '<li><strong>Step 2</strong> (target: March 15): '
                         'Update our <a '
                         'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/conduct/enforcement-manual/">Enforcement '
                         'Manual</a>, <a '
                         'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/conduct/reporting/">Reporting '
                         'Guidelines</a>, and <a '
                         'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/conduct/faq/">FAQs</a> '
                         'via <a '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/code-of-conduct/pull/91">pull '
                         'request 91</a>.</li>\n'
                         '<li><strong>Step 3</strong> (target: April 15): '
                         'Adopt the Contributor Covenant 3 with proposed '
                         'changes from the working group.</li>\n'
                         '</ul>\n'
                         '<p>Each step will have its own pull request where '
                         'the community can review and provide feedback before '
                         "we merge. We're committed to taking the time needed "
                         'to incorporate your input thoughtfully.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Thank you for being part of this important work '
                         'to make Django a more welcoming and inclusive '
                         'community for everyone!</p>',
              'summary_detail': {'base': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/rss/weblog/',
                                 'language': 'en',
                                 'type': 'text/html',
                                 'value': '<p>Last month <a '
                                          'href="https://forum.djangoproject.com/t/updating-the-code-of-conduct/43924">we '
                                          'announced our plan</a> to adopt <a '
                                          'href="https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/3/0/code_of_conduct/">Contributor '
                                          "Covenant 3</a> as Django's new Code "
                                          'of Conduct through a multi-step '
                                          "process. Today we're excited to "
                                          "share that we've completed the "
                                          'first step of that journey!</p>\n'
                                          '<h4 id="s-what-weve-done">What '
                                          "We've Done</h4>\n"
                                          "<p>We've merged <a "
                                          'href="https://github.com/django/code-of-conduct/blob/main/updates.md">new '
                                          'documentation</a> that outlines how '
                                          'any member of the Django community '
                                          'can propose changes to our Code of '
                                          'Conduct and related policies. This '
                                          'creates a transparent, '
                                          'community-driven process for '
                                          'keeping our policies current and '
                                          'relevant.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>The new process includes:</p>\n'
                                          '<ul>\n'
                                          '<li><strong>Proposing '
                                          'Changes</strong>: Anyone can <a '
                                          'href="https://github.com/django/code-of-conduct/issues/new?template=coc-change-proposal.md">open '
                                          'an issue</a> with a clear '
                                          'description of their proposed '
                                          'change and the rationale behind '
                                          'it.</li>\n'
                                          '<li><strong>Community '
                                          'Review</strong>: The Code of '
                                          'Conduct Working Group will discuss '
                                          'proposals in our monthly meetings '
                                          'and may solicit broader community '
                                          'feedback through the forum, '
                                          'Discord, or DSF Slack.</li>\n'
                                          '<li><strong>Approval and '
                                          'Announcement</strong>: Once '
                                          'consensus is reached, changes are '
                                          'merged and announced to the '
                                          'community. Changes to the Code of '
                                          'Conduct itself will be sent to the '
                                          'DSF Board for final approval.</li>\n'
                                          '</ul>\n'
                                          '<h4 '
                                          'id="s-how-you-can-get-involved">How '
                                          'You Can Get Involved</h4>\n'
                                          '<p>We welcome and encourage '
                                          'participation from everyone in the '
                                          "Django community! Here's how you "
                                          'can engage with this process:</p>\n'
                                          '<ul>\n'
                                          '<li><strong>Share Your '
                                          'Ideas</strong>: If you have '
                                          'suggestions for improving our Code '
                                          'of Conduct or related '
                                          'documentation, <a '
                                          'href="https://github.com/django/code-of-conduct/issues/new?template=coc-change-proposal.md">open '
                                          'an issue</a> on our GitHub '
                                          'repo.</li>\n'
                                          '<li><strong>Join the '
                                          'Discussion</strong>: Participate in '
                                          'community discussions about '
                                          'proposed changes on the forum, '
                                          'Discord, or DSF Slack. Keep it '
                                          'positive, constructive, and '
                                          'respectful.</li>\n'
                                          '<li><strong>Stay Informed</strong>: '
                                          'Watch the <a '
                                          'href="https://github.com/django/code-of-conduct">Code '
                                          'of Conduct repository</a> to follow '
                                          'along with proposed changes and '
                                          'discussions.</li>\n'
                                          '<li><strong>Provide '
                                          'Feedback</strong>: Not comfortable '
                                          'with GitHub? You can also reach out '
                                          'via <a '
                                          'href="mailto:conduct@djangoproject.com">conduct@djangoproject.com</a>, '
                                          'or look for anyone with the '
                                          '<code>Code of Conduct WG</code> '
                                          'role on Discord.</li>\n'
                                          '</ul>\n'
                                          '<h4 id="s-whats-next">What\'s '
                                          'Next</h4>\n'
                                          "<p>We're moving forward with the "
                                          'remaining steps of our plan:</p>\n'
                                          '<ul>\n'
                                          '<li><strong>Step 2</strong> '
                                          '(target: March 15): Update our <a '
                                          'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/conduct/enforcement-manual/">Enforcement '
                                          'Manual</a>, <a '
                                          'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/conduct/reporting/">Reporting '
                                          'Guidelines</a>, and <a '
                                          'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/conduct/faq/">FAQs</a> '
                                          'via <a '
                                          'href="https://github.com/django/code-of-conduct/pull/91">pull '
                                          'request 91</a>.</li>\n'
                                          '<li><strong>Step 3</strong> '
                                          '(target: April 15): Adopt the '
                                          'Contributor Covenant 3 with '
                                          'proposed changes from the working '
                                          'group.</li>\n'
                                          '</ul>\n'
                                          '<p>Each step will have its own pull '
                                          'request where the community can '
                                          'review and provide feedback before '
                                          "we merge. We're committed to taking "
                                          'the time needed to incorporate your '
                                          'input thoughtfully.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Thank you for being part of this '
                                          'important work to make Django a '
                                          'more welcoming and inclusive '
                                          'community for everyone!</p>'},
              'title': 'Plan to Adopt Contributor Covenant 3 as Django’s New '
                       'Code of Conduct',
              'title_detail': {'base': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/rss/weblog/',
                               'language': 'en',
                               'type': 'text/plain',
                               'value': 'Plan to Adopt Contributor Covenant 3 '
                                        'as Django’s New Code of Conduct'}},
             {'author': 'Frank Wiles',
              'author_detail': {'name': 'Frank Wiles'},
              'authors': [{'name': 'Frank Wiles'}],
              'guidislink': False,
              'id': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/weblog/2026/feb/11/steering-council-2025-year-in-review/',
              'link': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/weblog/2026/feb/11/steering-council-2025-year-in-review/',
              'links': [{'href': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/weblog/2026/feb/11/steering-council-2025-year-in-review/',
                         'rel': 'alternate',
                         'type': 'text/html'}],
              'published': 'Wed, 11 Feb 2026 08:44:22 -0600',
              'published_parsed': time.struct_time(tm_year=2026, tm_mon=2, tm_mday=11, tm_hour=14, tm_min=44, tm_sec=22, tm_wday=2, tm_yday=42, tm_isdst=0),
              'summary': '<p>The members of the Steering Council wanted to '
                         'provide you all with a \n'
                         'quick TL;DR of our work in 2025.  </p>\n'
                         '<p>First off, we were elected at the end of 2024 and '
                         'got started in earnest \n'
                         'in early 2025 with the mission to revive and '
                         'dramatically increase the role \n'
                         'of the Steering Council. </p>\n'
                         "<p>We're meeting for a video conference at least "
                         'monthly, you can deep dive \n'
                         'into the <a '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/steering-council/tree/main/meetings">meeting '
                         "notes</a> to see what we've been up to.  We also "
                         'have set up Slack channels we use to communicate in '
                         'between meetings to keep action items moving along.  '
                         '</p>\n'
                         '<p>One of the first things we did was temporarily '
                         'suspend much of the \n'
                         'process around <a '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/deps/blob/main/final/0010-new-governance.rst">DEP '
                         "10</a>.  Its heart is in the right place, but it's "
                         'just too complex and cumbersome day-to-day with a '
                         "primarily volunteer organization.  We're slowly "
                         'making progress on a revamped and simplified '
                         'process \n'
                         'that addresses our concerns.  It is our goal to '
                         'finish this before our terms expire. </p>\n'
                         '<h4 id="s-new-features-process">New Features '
                         'Process</h4>\n'
                         "<p>We've moved the process for proposing new "
                         'features out of the Django Forum and mailing lists '
                         'to  <a '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/new-features/issues">new-features '
                         'Github repository</a>.   </p>\n'
                         '<p>We made this change for a variety of reasons, but '
                         'the largest being to reduce the \n'
                         'workload for the Django Fellows in shepherding the '
                         'process and answering related questions. </p>\n'
                         '<h4 id="s-community-ecosystem-page">Community '
                         'Ecosystem Page</h4>\n'
                         '<p>One of our main goals is to increase the '
                         'visibility of the amazing Django third-party package '
                         'ecosystem. \n'
                         'Long time Django users know which packages to use, '
                         'which you can trust, and which ones may be perfect '
                         'for \n'
                         'certain use cases.  However, MANY newer or more '
                         'casual Django users are often unaware of these great '
                         'tools \n'
                         'and not sure where to even begin.  </p>\n'
                         "<p>As a first step, we've added the <a "
                         'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/community/ecosystem/">Community '
                         'Ecosystem</a> page \n'
                         'which highlights several amazing resources to keep '
                         'in touch with what is going on with Django, how to '
                         'find \n'
                         'recommended packages, and a sample list of those '
                         'packages the Steering Council itself recommends and '
                         'uses \n'
                         'frequently.   </p>\n'
                         '<h4 id="s-administrative-bits">Administrative '
                         'bits</h4>\n'
                         '<p>There has been work on better formalizing and '
                         'documenting our processes and building documentation '
                         'to make \n'
                         'it much easier for the next Steering Council '
                         'members.  </p>\n'
                         '<p>There has also been fair bit of work around '
                         'helping organize Google Summer of Code participants '
                         'to \n'
                         'help ensure the projects undertaken are ones that '
                         'will ultimately be accepted smoothly into Django. '
                         '</p>\n'
                         '<p>Another area we have focused on is a simplified '
                         "DEP process.  We're still formalizing this, but the "
                         'idea is to \n'
                         'have the Steering Council do the majority of the '
                         'heavy lifting on writing these and in a format that '
                         'is shorter/simpler \n'
                         'to reduce the friction of creating larger more '
                         'complicated DEPs. </p>\n'
                         '<p>We have also been in discussions with various '
                         'third parties about acquiring funding for some of '
                         'the new features \n'
                         'and updates on the horizon.  </p>\n'
                         "<p>It's been a productive year and we're aiming to "
                         "have 2026 be as productive if not more so.  We're "
                         'still setting \n'
                         'all of our 2026 goals and will report on those '
                         'soon.  </p>\n'
                         '<p>Please reach out to the Steering Council directly '
                         'if you have any questions or concerns.</p>',
              'summary_detail': {'base': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/rss/weblog/',
