                                          'uses \n'
                                          'frequently.   </p>\n'
                                          '<h4 '
                                          'id="s-administrative-bits">Administrative '
                                          'bits</h4>\n'
                                          '<p>There has been work on better '
                                          'formalizing and documenting our '
                                          'processes and building '
                                          'documentation to make \n'
                                          'it much easier for the next '
                                          'Steering Council members.  </p>\n'
                                          '<p>There has also been fair bit of '
                                          'work around helping organize Google '
                                          'Summer of Code participants to \n'
                                          'help ensure the projects undertaken '
                                          'are ones that will ultimately be '
                                          'accepted smoothly into Django. '
                                          '</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Another area we have focused on '
                                          "is a simplified DEP process.  We're "
                                          'still formalizing this, but the '
                                          'idea is to \n'
                                          'have the Steering Council do the '
                                          'majority of the heavy lifting on '
                                          'writing these and in a format that '
                                          'is shorter/simpler \n'
                                          'to reduce the friction of creating '
                                          'larger more complicated DEPs. </p>\n'
                                          '<p>We have also been in discussions '
                                          'with various third parties about '
                                          'acquiring funding for some of the '
                                          'new features \n'
                                          'and updates on the horizon.  </p>\n'
                                          "<p>It's been a productive year and "
                                          "we're aiming to have 2026 be as "
                                          "productive if not more so.  We're "
                                          'still setting \n'
                                          'all of our 2026 goals and will '
                                          'report on those soon.  </p>\n'
                                          '<p>Please reach out to the Steering '
                                          'Council directly if you have any '
                                          'questions or concerns.</p>'},
              'title': 'Django Steering Council 2025 Year in Review',
              'title_detail': {'base': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/rss/weblog/',
                               'language': 'en',
                               'type': 'text/plain',
                               'value': 'Django Steering Council 2025 Year in '
                                        'Review'}},
             {'author': 'Jacob Walls',
              'author_detail': {'name': 'Jacob Walls'},
              'authors': [{'name': 'Jacob Walls'}],
              'guidislink': False,
              'id': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/weblog/2026/feb/04/recent-trends-security-team/',
              'link': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/weblog/2026/feb/04/recent-trends-security-team/',
              'links': [{'href': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/weblog/2026/feb/04/recent-trends-security-team/',
                         'rel': 'alternate',
                         'type': 'text/html'}],
              'published': 'Wed, 04 Feb 2026 10:00:00 -0600',
              'published_parsed': time.struct_time(tm_year=2026, tm_mon=2, tm_mday=4, tm_hour=16, tm_min=0, tm_sec=0, tm_wday=2, tm_yday=35, tm_isdst=0),
              'summary': '<p>Yesterday, Django <a '
                         'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/weblog/2026/feb/03/security-releases/">issued '
                         'security releases</a> mitigating six vulnerabilities '
                         'of varying severity. Django is a secure web '
                         'framework, and that hasn’t changed. What feels new '
                         'is the remarkable consistency across the reports we '
                         'receive now.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Almost every report now is a variation on a prior '
                         'vulnerability. Instead of uncovering new classes of '
                         'issues, these reports explore how an underlying '
                         'pattern from a recent advisory might surface in a '
                         'similar code path or under a slightly different '
                         'configuration. These reports are often technically '
                         'plausible but only sometimes worth fixing. Over '
                         'time, this has shifted the Security Team’s work away '
                         'from discovery towards deciding how far a given '
                         'precedent should extend and whether the impact of '
                         'the marginal variation rises to the level of a '
                         'vulnerability.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Take yesterday’s releases:</p>\n'
                         '<p>We patched a “low” severity user enumeration '
                         'vulnerability in the <code>mod_wsgi</code> '
                         'authentication handler (<a '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#february-3-2026-cve-2025-13473">CVE '
                         '2025-13473</a>). It’s a straightforward variation on '
                         '<a '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#july-9-2024-cve-2024-39329">CVE '
                         '2024-39329</a>, which affected authentication more '
                         'generally.</p>\n'
                         '<p>We also patched two potential denial-of-service '
                         'vulnerabilities when handling large, malformed '
                         'inputs. One exploits inefficient string '
                         'concatenation in header parsing under ASGI (<a '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#february-3-2026-cve-2025-14550">CVE '
                         '2025-14550</a>). Concatenating strings in a loop is '
                         'known to be slow, and we’ve done <a '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/pull/20045/changes/ad94446fcc5b50401dd0c48718502d5d1b92df58">fixes</a> '
                         'in public where the impact is low. The other one (<a '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#february-3-2026-cve-2026-1285">CVE '
                         '2026-1285</a>) exploits deeply nested entities. '
                         'December’s vulnerability in the XML serializer (<a '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#december-2-2025-cve-2025-64460">CVE '
                         '2025-64460</a>) was about those very two '
                         'themes.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Finally, we also patched three potential SQL '
                         'injection vulnerabilities. One envisioned a '
                         'developer passing unsanitized user input to a niche '
                         'feature of the PostGIS backend (<a '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#february-3-2026-cve-2026-1207">CVE '
                         '2026-1207</a>), much like <a '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#march-4-2020-cve-2020-9402">CVE '
                         '2020-9402</a>. Our <a '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/internals/security/#user-input-must-be-sanitized">security '
                         'reporting policy</a> assumes that developers are '
                         'aware of the risks when passing unsanitized user '
                         'input directly to the ORM. But the division between '
                         'SQL statements and parameters is well ingrained, and '
                         'the expectation is that Django will not fail to '
                         'escape parameters. The last two vulnerabilities (<a '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#february-3-2026-cve-2026-1287">CVE '
                         '2026-1287</a> and <a '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#february-3-2026-cve-2026-1312">CVE '
                         '2026-1312</a>) targeted user-controlled column '
                         'aliases, the latest in a stream of reports stemming '
                         'from <a '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#april-11-2022-cve-2022-28346">CVE '
                         '2022-28346</a>, involving unpacking '
                         '<code>**kwargs</code> into <code>.filter()</code> '
                         'and friends, including four security releases in a '
                         'row in late 2025. You might ask, “who would unpack '
                         '<code>**kwargs</code> into the ORM?!” But imagine '
                         'letting users name aggregations in configurable '
                         'reports. You would have something more like a '
                         'parameter, and so you would appreciate some '
                         'protection against crafted inputs.</p>\n'
                         '<p>On top of all that, on a nearly daily basis we '
                         'get reports duplicating other pending reports, or '
                         'even reports about vulnerabilities that have already '
                         'been fixed and publicized. Clearly, reporters are '
                         'using LLMs to generate (initially) plausible '
                         'variations.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Security releases come with costs to the '
                         'community. They interrupt our users’ development '
                         'workflows, and they also severely interrupt '
                         'ours.</p>\n'
                         '<p>There are alternatives. The long tail of reports '
                         'about user-controlled aliases presents an obvious '
                         'one: we can just re-architect that area. (Thanks to '
                         'Simon Charette for a <a '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/pull/20587">pull '
                         'request</a> doing just that!) Beyond that, there are '
                         'more drastic alternatives. We can confirm fewer '
                         'vulnerabilities by placing a higher value on a '
                         "user's duty to validate inputs, placing a lower "
                         'value on our prior precedents, or fixing lower '
                         'severity issues publicly. The risk there is '
                         'underreacting, or seeing our development workflow '
                         'disrupted anyway when a decision not to confirm a '
                         'vulnerability is challenged.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Reporters are clearly benefiting from our '
                         'commitment to being consistent. For the moment, the '
                         'Security Team hopes that reacting in a consistent '
                         'way—even if it means sometimes issuing six '
                         'patches—outweighs the cost of the security process. '
                         'It’s something we’re weighing.</p>\n'
                         '<p>As always, keep the responsibly vetted reports '
                         'coming to security@djangoproject.com.</p>',
              'summary_detail': {'base': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/rss/weblog/',
                                 'language': 'en',
                                 'type': 'text/html',
                                 'value': '<p>Yesterday, Django <a '
                                          'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/weblog/2026/feb/03/security-releases/">issued '
                                          'security releases</a> mitigating '
                                          'six vulnerabilities of varying '
                                          'severity. Django is a secure web '
                                          'framework, and that hasn’t changed. '
                                          'What feels new is the remarkable '
                                          'consistency across the reports we '
                                          'receive now.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Almost every report now is a '
                                          'variation on a prior vulnerability. '
                                          'Instead of uncovering new classes '
                                          'of issues, these reports explore '
                                          'how an underlying pattern from a '
                                          'recent advisory might surface in a '
                                          'similar code path or under a '
                                          'slightly different configuration. '
                                          'These reports are often technically '
                                          'plausible but only sometimes worth '
                                          'fixing. Over time, this has shifted '
                                          'the Security Team’s work away from '
                                          'discovery towards deciding how far '
                                          'a given precedent should extend and '
                                          'whether the impact of the marginal '
                                          'variation rises to the level of a '
                                          'vulnerability.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Take yesterday’s releases:</p>\n'
                                          '<p>We patched a “low” severity user '
                                          'enumeration vulnerability in the '
                                          '<code>mod_wsgi</code> '
                                          'authentication handler (<a '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#february-3-2026-cve-2025-13473">CVE '
                                          '2025-13473</a>). It’s a '
                                          'straightforward variation on <a '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#july-9-2024-cve-2024-39329">CVE '
                                          '2024-39329</a>, which affected '
                                          'authentication more generally.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>We also patched two potential '
                                          'denial-of-service vulnerabilities '
                                          'when handling large, malformed '
                                          'inputs. One exploits inefficient '
                                          'string concatenation in header '
                                          'parsing under ASGI (<a '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#february-3-2026-cve-2025-14550">CVE '
                                          '2025-14550</a>). Concatenating '
                                          'strings in a loop is known to be '
                                          'slow, and we’ve done <a '
                                          'href="https://github.com/django/django/pull/20045/changes/ad94446fcc5b50401dd0c48718502d5d1b92df58">fixes</a> '
                                          'in public where the impact is low. '
                                          'The other one (<a '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#february-3-2026-cve-2026-1285">CVE '
                                          '2026-1285</a>) exploits deeply '
                                          'nested entities. December’s '
                                          'vulnerability in the XML serializer '
                                          '(<a '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#december-2-2025-cve-2025-64460">CVE '
                                          '2025-64460</a>) was about those '
                                          'very two themes.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Finally, we also patched three '
                                          'potential SQL injection '
                                          'vulnerabilities. One envisioned a '
                                          'developer passing unsanitized user '
                                          'input to a niche feature of the '
                                          'PostGIS backend (<a '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#february-3-2026-cve-2026-1207">CVE '
                                          '2026-1207</a>), much like <a '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#march-4-2020-cve-2020-9402">CVE '
                                          '2020-9402</a>. Our <a '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/internals/security/#user-input-must-be-sanitized">security '
                                          'reporting policy</a> assumes that '
                                          'developers are aware of the risks '
                                          'when passing unsanitized user input '
                                          'directly to the ORM. But the '
                                          'division between SQL statements and '
                                          'parameters is well ingrained, and '
                                          'the expectation is that Django will '
                                          'not fail to escape parameters. The '
                                          'last two vulnerabilities (<a '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#february-3-2026-cve-2026-1287">CVE '
                                          '2026-1287</a> and <a '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#february-3-2026-cve-2026-1312">CVE '
                                          '2026-1312</a>) targeted '
                                          'user-controlled column aliases, the '
                                          'latest in a stream of reports '
                                          'stemming from <a '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/releases/security/#april-11-2022-cve-2022-28346">CVE '
                                          '2022-28346</a>, involving unpacking '
                                          '<code>**kwargs</code> into '
                                          '<code>.filter()</code> and friends, '
                                          'including four security releases in '
                                          'a row in late 2025. You might ask, '
                                          '“who would unpack '
                                          '<code>**kwargs</code> into the '
                                          'ORM?!” But imagine letting users '
                                          'name aggregations in configurable '
                                          'reports. You would have something '
                                          'more like a parameter, and so you '
                                          'would appreciate some protection '
                                          'against crafted inputs.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>On top of all that, on a nearly '
                                          'daily basis we get reports '
                                          'duplicating other pending reports, '
                                          'or even reports about '
                                          'vulnerabilities that have already '
                                          'been fixed and publicized. Clearly, '
                                          'reporters are using LLMs to '
                                          'generate (initially) plausible '
                                          'variations.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Security releases come with '
                                          'costs to the community. They '
                                          'interrupt our users’ development '
                                          'workflows, and they also severely '
                                          'interrupt ours.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>There are alternatives. The long '
                                          'tail of reports about '
                                          'user-controlled aliases presents an '
                                          'obvious one: we can just '
                                          're-architect that area. (Thanks to '
                                          'Simon Charette for a <a '
                                          'href="https://github.com/django/django/pull/20587">pull '
                                          'request</a> doing just that!) '
                                          'Beyond that, there are more drastic '
                                          'alternatives. We can confirm fewer '
                                          'vulnerabilities by placing a higher '
                                          "value on a user's duty to validate "
                                          'inputs, placing a lower value on '
                                          'our prior precedents, or fixing '
                                          'lower severity issues publicly. The '
                                          'risk there is underreacting, or '
                                          'seeing our development workflow '
                                          'disrupted anyway when a decision '
                                          'not to confirm a vulnerability is '
                                          'challenged.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Reporters are clearly benefiting '
                                          'from our commitment to being '
                                          'consistent. For the moment, the '
                                          'Security Team hopes that reacting '
                                          'in a consistent way—even if it '
                                          'means sometimes issuing six '
                                          'patches—outweighs the cost of the '
                                          'security process. It’s something '
                                          'we’re weighing.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>As always, keep the responsibly '
                                          'vetted reports coming to '
                                          'security@djangoproject.com.</p>'},
              'title': 'Recent trends in the work of the Django Security Team',
              'title_detail': {'base': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/rss/weblog/',
                               'language': 'en',
                               'type': 'text/plain',
                               'value': 'Recent trends in the work of the '
                                        'Django Security Team'}},
             {'author': 'Jacob Walls',
              'author_detail': {'name': 'Jacob Walls'},
              'authors': [{'name': 'Jacob Walls'}],
              'guidislink': False,
              'id': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/weblog/2026/feb/03/security-releases/',
              'link': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/weblog/2026/feb/03/security-releases/',
              'links': [{'href': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/weblog/2026/feb/03/security-releases/',
                         'rel': 'alternate',
                         'type': 'text/html'}],
              'published': 'Tue, 03 Feb 2026 08:13:48 -0600',
              'published_parsed': time.struct_time(tm_year=2026, tm_mon=2, tm_mday=3, tm_hour=14, tm_min=13, tm_sec=48, tm_wday=1, tm_yday=34, tm_isdst=0),
              'summary': '<p>In accordance with <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/internals/security/">our '
                         'security release policy</a>, the Django team\n'
                         'is issuing releases for\n'
                         '<a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/releases/6.0.2/">Django '
                         '6.0.2</a>,\n'
                         '<a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/releases/5.2.11/">Django '
                         '5.2.11</a>, and\n'
                         '<a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/releases/4.2.28/">Django '
                         '4.2.28</a>.\n'
                         'These releases address the security issues detailed '
                         'below. We encourage all\n'
                         'users of Django to upgrade as soon as possible.</p>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2025-13473-username-enumeration-through-timing-difference-in-mod-wsgi-authentication-handler">\n'
                         '<h3>CVE-2025-13473: Username enumeration through '
                         'timing difference in mod_wsgi authentication '
                         'handler</h3>\n'
                         '<p>The <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">django.contrib.auth.handlers.modwsgi.check_password()</tt> '
                         'function for authentication via <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">mod_wsgi</tt> allowed remote attackers to '
                         'enumerate users via a timing attack.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Thanks to Stackered for the report.</p>\n'
                         '<p>This issue has severity &quot;low&quot; according '
                         'to the Django security policy.</p>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2025-14550-potential-denial-of-service-vulnerability-via-repeated-headers-when-using-asgi">\n'
                         '<h3>CVE-2025-14550: Potential denial-of-service '
                         'vulnerability via repeated headers when using '
                         'ASGI</h3>\n'
                         '<p>When receiving duplicates of a single header, <tt '
                         'class="docutils literal">ASGIRequest</tt> allowed a '
                         'remote attacker to cause a potential '
                         'denial-of-service via a specifically created request '
                         'with multiple duplicate headers. The vulnerability '
                         'resulted from repeated string concatenation while '
                         'combining repeated headers, which\n'
                         'produced super-linear computation resulting in '
                         'service degradation or outage.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Thanks to Jiyong Yang for the report.</p>\n'
                         '<p>This issue has severity &quot;moderate&quot; '
                         'according to the Django security policy.</p>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2026-1207-potential-sql-injection-via-raster-lookups-on-postgis">\n'
                         '<h3>CVE-2026-1207: Potential SQL injection via '
                         'raster lookups on PostGIS</h3>\n'
                         '<p>Raster lookups on GIS fields (only implemented on '
                         'PostGIS) were subject to SQL injection if untrusted '
                         'data was used as a band index.</p>\n'
                         '<p>As a reminder, all untrusted user input should be '
                         'validated before use.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Thanks to Tarek Nakkouch for the report.</p>\n'
                         '<p>This issue has severity &quot;high&quot; '
                         'according to the Django security policy.</p>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2026-1285-potential-denial-of-service-vulnerability-in-django-utils-text-truncator-html-methods">\n'
                         '<h3>CVE-2026-1285: Potential denial-of-service '
                         'vulnerability in <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">django.utils.text.Truncator</tt> HTML '
                         'methods</h3>\n'
                         '<p><tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">django.utils.text.Truncator.chars()</tt> '
                         'and <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">Truncator.words()</tt> methods (with <tt '
                         'class="docutils literal">html=True</tt>) and <tt '
                         'class="docutils literal">truncatechars_html</tt> and '
                         '<tt class="docutils literal">truncatewords_html</tt> '
                         'template filters were subject to a potential '
                         'denial-of-service attack via certain inputs with a '
                         'large number of unmatched HTML end tags, which could '
                         'cause quadratic time complexity during HTML '
                         'parsing.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Thanks to Seokchan Yoon for the report.</p>\n'
                         '<p>This issue has severity &quot;moderate&quot; '
                         'according to the Django security policy.</p>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2026-1287-potential-sql-injection-in-column-aliases-via-control-characters">\n'
                         '<h3>CVE-2026-1287: Potential SQL injection in column '
                         'aliases via control characters</h3>\n'
                         '<p><tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">FilteredRelation</tt> was subject to SQL '
                         'injection in column aliases via control characters, '
                         'using a suitably crafted dictionary, with dictionary '
                         'expansion, as the <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">**kwargs</tt> passed to <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">QuerySet</tt> methods <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">annotate()</tt>, <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">aggregate()</tt>, <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">extra()</tt>, <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">values()</tt>, <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">values_list()</tt>, and <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">alias()</tt>.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Thanks to Solomon Kebede for the report.</p>\n'
                         '<p>This issue has severity &quot;high&quot; '
                         'according to the Django security policy.</p>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2026-1312-potential-sql-injection-via-queryset-order-by-and-filteredrelation">\n'
                         '<h3>CVE-2026-1312: Potential SQL injection via <tt '
                         'class="docutils literal">QuerySet.order_by</tt> and '
                         '<tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">FilteredRelation</tt></h3>\n'
                         '<p><tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">QuerySet.order_by()</tt> was subject to SQL '
                         'injection in column aliases containing periods when '
                         'the same alias was, using a suitably crafted '
                         'dictionary, with dictionary expansion, used in <tt '
                         'class="docutils literal">FilteredRelation</tt>.</p>\n'
                         '<p>Thanks to Solomon Kebede for the report.</p>\n'
                         '<p>This issue has severity &quot;high&quot; '
                         'according to the Django security policy.</p>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-affected-supported-versions">\n'
                         '<h3>Affected supported versions</h3>\n'
                         '<ul class="simple">\n'
                         '<li>Django main</li>\n'
                         '<li>Django 6.0</li>\n'
                         '<li>Django 5.2</li>\n'
                         '<li>Django 4.2</li>\n'
                         '</ul>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" id="s-resolution">\n'
                         '<h3>Resolution</h3>\n'
                         '<p>Patches to resolve the issue have been applied to '
                         "Django's\n"
                         'main, 6.0, 5.2, and 4.2 branches.\n'
                         'The patches may be obtained from the following '
                         'changesets.</p>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2025-13473-username-enumeration-through-timing-difference-in-mod-wsgi-authentication-handler-1">\n'
                         '<h4>CVE-2025-13473: Username enumeration through '
                         'timing difference in mod_wsgi authentication '
                         'handler</h4>\n'
                         '<ul class="simple">\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/3eb814e02a4c336866d4189fa0c24fd1875863ed">main '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/d72cc3be3be0bbebdcaea5a8c8106b4d6f2a32bd">6.0 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/184e38ab0a061c365f5775676a074796d8abd02f">5.2 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/6dc23508f3395e1254c315084c7334ef81c4c09a">4.2 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '</ul>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2025-14550-potential-denial-of-service-vulnerability-via-repeated-headers-when-using-asgi-1">\n'
                         '<h4>CVE-2025-14550: Potential denial-of-service '
                         'vulnerability via repeated headers when using '
                         'ASGI</h4>\n'
                         '<ul class="simple">\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/eb22e1d6d643360e952609ef562c139a100ea4eb">main '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/972dbdd4f7f69e9c405e6fe12a1b90e4713c1611">6.0 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/1ba90069c12836db46981bdf75b0e661db5849ce">5.2 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/f578acc8c54530fffabd52d2db654c8669b011af">4.2 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '</ul>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2026-1207-potential-sql-injection-via-raster-lookups-on-postgis-1">\n'
                         '<h4>CVE-2026-1207: Potential SQL injection via '
                         'raster lookups on PostGIS</h4>\n'
                         '<ul class="simple">\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/81aa5292967cd09319c45fe2c1a525ce7b6684d8">main '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/8f77e7301174834573614ae90e1826fdf27f8a24">6.0 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/17a1d64a58ef24c0c3b78d66d86f5415075f18f0">5.2 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/a14363102d98fa29b8cced578eb3a0fadaa5bcb7">4.2 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '</ul>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2026-1285-potential-denial-of-service-vulnerability-in-django-utils-text-truncator-html-methods-1">\n'
                         '<h4>CVE-2026-1285: Potential denial-of-service '
                         'vulnerability in <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">django.utils.text.Truncator</tt> HTML '
                         'methods</h4>\n'
                         '<ul class="simple">\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/a33540b3e20b5d759aa8b2e4b9ca0e8edd285344">main '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/4b86ba51e486530db982341a23e53c7a1e1e6e71">6.0 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/9f2ada875bbee62ac46032e38ddb22755d67ae5a">5.2 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/b40cfc6052ced26dcd8166a58ea6f841d0d2cac8">4.2 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '</ul>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2026-1287-potential-sql-injection-in-column-aliases-via-control-characters-1">\n'
                         '<h4>CVE-2026-1287: Potential SQL injection in column '
                         'aliases via control characters</h4>\n'
                         '<ul class="simple">\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/e891a84c7ef9962bfcc3b4685690219542f86a22">main '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/0c0f5c2178c01ada5410cd53b4b207bf7858b952">6.0 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/3e68ccdc11c127758745ddf0b4954990b14892bc">5.2 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/f75f8f3597e1ce351d5ac08b6ba7ebd9dadd9b5d">4.2 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '</ul>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-cve-2026-1312-potential-sql-injection-via-queryset-order-by-and-filteredrelation-1">\n'
                         '<h4>CVE-2026-1312: Potential SQL injection via <tt '
                         'class="docutils literal">QuerySet.order_by</tt> and '
                         '<tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">FilteredRelation</tt></h4>\n'
                         '<ul class="simple">\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/69065ca869b0970dff8fdd8fafb390bf8b3bf222">main '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/15e70cb83e6f7a9a2a2f651f30b28b5cb20febeb">6.0 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/e863ee273c6553e9b6fa4960a17acb535851857b">5.2 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '<li>On the <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/90f5b10784ba5bf369caed87640e2b4394ea3314">4.2 '
                         'branch</a></li>\n'
                         '</ul>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-the-following-releases-have-been-issued">\n'
                         '<h3>The following releases have been issued</h3>\n'
                         '<ul class="simple">\n'
                         '<li>Django 6.0.2 (<a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/download/6.0.2/tarball/">download '
                         'Django 6.0.2</a> |\n'
                         '<a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/download/6.0.2/checksum/">6.0.2 '
                         'checksums</a>)</li>\n'
                         '<li>Django 5.2.11 (<a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/download/5.2.11/tarball/">download '
                         'Django 5.2.11</a> |\n'
                         '<a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/download/5.2.11/checksum/">5.2.11 '
                         'checksums</a>)</li>\n'
                         '<li>Django 4.2.28 (<a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/download/4.2.28/tarball/">download '
                         'Django 4.2.28</a> |\n'
                         '<a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/download/4.2.28/checksum/">4.2.28 '
                         'checksums</a>)</li>\n'
                         '</ul>\n'
                         '<p>The PGP key ID used for this release is Jacob '
                         'Walls: <a class="reference external" '
                         'href="https://github.com/jacobtylerwalls.gpg">131403F4D16D8DC7</a></p>\n'
                         '</div>\n'
                         '<div class="section" '
                         'id="s-general-notes-regarding-security-reporting">\n'
                         '<h3>General notes regarding security reporting</h3>\n'
                         '<p>As always, we ask that potential security issues '
                         'be reported via private email\n'
                         'to <tt class="docutils '
                         'literal">security&#64;djangoproject.com</tt>, and '
                         "not via Django's Trac instance, nor via\n"
                         'the Django Forum. Please see <a class="reference '
                         'external" '
                         'href="https://www.djangoproject.com/security/">our '
                         'security policies</a> for further information.</p>\n'
                         '</div>',
              'summary_detail': {'base': 'https://www.djangoproject.com/rss/weblog/',
                                 'language': 'en',
                                 'type': 'text/html',
                                 'value': '<p>In accordance with <a '
                                          'class="reference external" '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/internals/security/">our '
                                          'security release policy</a>, the '
                                          'Django team\n'
                                          'is issuing releases for\n'
                                          '<a class="reference external" '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/releases/6.0.2/">Django '
                                          '6.0.2</a>,\n'
                                          '<a class="reference external" '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/releases/5.2.11/">Django '
                                          '5.2.11</a>, and\n'
                                          '<a class="reference external" '
                                          'href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/releases/4.2.28/">Django '
                                          '4.2.28</a>.\n'
                                          'These releases address the security '
                                          'issues detailed below. We encourage '
                                          'all\n'
                                          'users of Django to upgrade as soon '
                                          'as possible.</p>\n'
                                          '<div class="section" '
                                          'id="s-cve-2025-13473-username-enumeration-through-timing-difference-in-mod-wsgi-authentication-handler">\n'
                                          '<h3>CVE-2025-13473: Username '
                                          'enumeration through timing '
                                          'difference in mod_wsgi '
                                          'authentication handler</h3>\n'
                                          '<p>The <tt class="docutils '
                                          'literal">django.contrib.auth.handlers.modwsgi.check_password()</tt> '
                                          'function for authentication via <tt '
                                          'class="docutils '
                                          'literal">mod_wsgi</tt> allowed '
                                          'remote attackers to enumerate users '
                                          'via a timing attack.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Thanks to Stackered for the '
                                          'report.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>This issue has severity '
                                          '&quot;low&quot; according to the '
                                          'Django security policy.</p>\n'
                                          '</div>\n'
                                          '<div class="section" '
                                          'id="s-cve-2025-14550-potential-denial-of-service-vulnerability-via-repeated-headers-when-using-asgi">\n'
                                          '<h3>CVE-2025-14550: Potential '
                                          'denial-of-service vulnerability via '
                                          'repeated headers when using '
                                          'ASGI</h3>\n'
                                          '<p>When receiving duplicates of a '
                                          'single header, <tt class="docutils '
                                          'literal">ASGIRequest</tt> allowed a '
                                          'remote attacker to cause a '
                                          'potential denial-of-service via a '
                                          'specifically created request with '
                                          'multiple duplicate headers. The '
                                          'vulnerability resulted from '
                                          'repeated string concatenation while '
                                          'combining repeated headers, which\n'
                                          'produced super-linear computation '
                                          'resulting in service degradation or '
                                          'outage.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Thanks to Jiyong Yang for the '
                                          'report.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>This issue has severity '
                                          '&quot;moderate&quot; according to '
                                          'the Django security policy.</p>\n'
                                          '</div>\n'
                                          '<div class="section" '
                                          'id="s-cve-2026-1207-potential-sql-injection-via-raster-lookups-on-postgis">\n'
                                          '<h3>CVE-2026-1207: Potential SQL '
                                          'injection via raster lookups on '
                                          'PostGIS</h3>\n'
                                          '<p>Raster lookups on GIS fields '
                                          '(only implemented on PostGIS) were '
                                          'subject to SQL injection if '
                                          'untrusted data was used as a band '
                                          'index.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>As a reminder, all untrusted '
                                          'user input should be validated '
                                          'before use.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Thanks to Tarek Nakkouch for the '
                                          'report.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>This issue has severity '
                                          '&quot;high&quot; according to the '
                                          'Django security policy.</p>\n'
                                          '</div>\n'
                                          '<div class="section" '
                                          'id="s-cve-2026-1285-potential-denial-of-service-vulnerability-in-django-utils-text-truncator-html-methods">\n'
                                          '<h3>CVE-2026-1285: Potential '
                                          'denial-of-service vulnerability in '
                                          '<tt class="docutils '
                                          'literal">django.utils.text.Truncator</tt> '
                                          'HTML methods</h3>\n'
                                          '<p><tt class="docutils '
                                          'literal">django.utils.text.Truncator.chars()</tt> '
                                          'and <tt class="docutils '
                                          'literal">Truncator.words()</tt> '
                                          'methods (with <tt class="docutils '
                                          'literal">html=True</tt>) and <tt '
                                          'class="docutils '
                                          'literal">truncatechars_html</tt> '
                                          'and <tt class="docutils '
                                          'literal">truncatewords_html</tt> '
                                          'template filters were subject to a '
                                          'potential denial-of-service attack '
                                          'via certain inputs with a large '
                                          'number of unmatched HTML end tags, '
                                          'which could cause quadratic time '
                                          'complexity during HTML '
                                          'parsing.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Thanks to Seokchan Yoon for the '
                                          'report.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>This issue has severity '
                                          '&quot;moderate&quot; according to '
                                          'the Django security policy.</p>\n'
                                          '</div>\n'
                                          '<div class="section" '
                                          'id="s-cve-2026-1287-potential-sql-injection-in-column-aliases-via-control-characters">\n'
                                          '<h3>CVE-2026-1287: Potential SQL '
                                          'injection in column aliases via '
                                          'control characters</h3>\n'
                                          '<p><tt class="docutils '
                                          'literal">FilteredRelation</tt> was '
                                          'subject to SQL injection in column '
                                          'aliases via control characters, '
                                          'using a suitably crafted '
                                          'dictionary, with dictionary '
                                          'expansion, as the <tt '
                                          'class="docutils '
                                          'literal">**kwargs</tt> passed to '
                                          '<tt class="docutils '
                                          'literal">QuerySet</tt> methods <tt '
                                          'class="docutils '
                                          'literal">annotate()</tt>, <tt '
                                          'class="docutils '
                                          'literal">aggregate()</tt>, <tt '
                                          'class="docutils '
                                          'literal">extra()</tt>, <tt '
                                          'class="docutils '
                                          'literal">values()</tt>, <tt '
                                          'class="docutils '
                                          'literal">values_list()</tt>, and '
                                          '<tt class="docutils '
                                          'literal">alias()</tt>.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Thanks to Solomon Kebede for the '
                                          'report.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>This issue has severity '
                                          '&quot;high&quot; according to the '
                                          'Django security policy.</p>\n'
                                          '</div>\n'
                                          '<div class="section" '
                                          'id="s-cve-2026-1312-potential-sql-injection-via-queryset-order-by-and-filteredrelation">\n'
                                          '<h3>CVE-2026-1312: Potential SQL '
                                          'injection via <tt class="docutils '
                                          'literal">QuerySet.order_by</tt> and '
                                          '<tt class="docutils '
                                          'literal">FilteredRelation</tt></h3>\n'
                                          '<p><tt class="docutils '
                                          'literal">QuerySet.order_by()</tt> '
                                          'was subject to SQL injection in '
                                          'column aliases containing periods '
                                          'when the same alias was, using a '
                                          'suitably crafted dictionary, with '
                                          'dictionary expansion, used in <tt '
                                          'class="docutils '
                                          'literal">FilteredRelation</tt>.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>Thanks to Solomon Kebede for the '
                                          'report.</p>\n'
                                          '<p>This issue has severity '
                                          '&quot;high&quot; according to the '
                                          'Django security policy.</p>\n'
                                          '</div>\n'
                                          '<div class="section" '
                                          'id="s-affected-supported-versions">\n'
                                          '<h3>Affected supported '
                                          'versions</h3>\n'
                                          '<ul class="simple">\n'
                                          '<li>Django main</li>\n'
                                          '<li>Django 6.0</li>\n'
                                          '<li>Django 5.2</li>\n'
                                          '<li>Django 4.2</li>\n'
                                          '</ul>\n'
                                          '</div>\n'
                                          '<div class="section" '
                                          'id="s-resolution">\n'
                                          '<h3>Resolution</h3>\n'
                                          '<p>Patches to resolve the issue '
                                          "have been applied to Django's\n"
                                          'main, 6.0, 5.2, and 4.2 branches.\n'
                                          'The patches may be obtained from '
                                          'the following changesets.</p>\n'
                                          '<div class="section" '
                                          'id="s-cve-2025-13473-username-enumeration-through-timing-difference-in-mod-wsgi-authentication-handler-1">\n'
                                          '<h4>CVE-2025-13473: Username '
                                          'enumeration through timing '
                                          'difference in mod_wsgi '
                                          'authentication handler</h4>\n'
                                          '<ul class="simple">\n'
                                          '<li>On the <a class="reference '
                                          'external" '
                                          'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/3eb814e02a4c336866d4189fa0c24fd1875863ed">main '
                                          'branch</a></li>\n'
                                          '<li>On the <a class="reference '
                                          'external" '
                                          'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/d72cc3be3be0bbebdcaea5a8c8106b4d6f2a32bd">6.0 '
                                          'branch</a></li>\n'
                                          '<li>On the <a class="reference '
                                          'external" '
                                          'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/184e38ab0a061c365f5775676a074796d8abd02f">5.2 '
                                          'branch</a></li>\n'
                                          '<li>On the <a class="reference '
                                          'external" '
                                          'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/6dc23508f3395e1254c315084c7334ef81c4c09a">4.2 '
                                          'branch</a></li>\n'
                                          '</ul>\n'
                                          '</div>\n'
                                          '<div class="section" '
                                          'id="s-cve-2025-14550-potential-denial-of-service-vulnerability-via-repeated-headers-when-using-asgi-1">\n'
                                          '<h4>CVE-2025-14550: Potential '
                                          'denial-of-service vulnerability via '
                                          'repeated headers when using '
                                          'ASGI</h4>\n'
                                          '<ul class="simple">\n'
                                          '<li>On the <a class="reference '
                                          'external" '
                                          'href="https://github.com/django/django/commit/eb22e1d6d643360e952609ef562c139a100ea4eb">main '
